result.name: Hong Kong Market - Yat Tung

reviews.text: This is my favourite wet market in Hong Kong. It was clean, well designed and have a nostalgic ambient vibe. The foods and fresh products are very welcome by local people. thumbs up for this wet market.

This is really a great market with a nice mixture of produce and food, air conditioned, very nicely arranged, making it near but still maintaining the soul of a market, with men and women covered in animal remains, freshly caught and cut. Really enjoyed it.
My favourite market in Tung Chung. It’s very cool, even has a huge 747 model hanging from the roof.
Decent market. Good price and selection.

Good. Unlike many other wet markets which are either untidy, crowded, dirty or modernized, this market brings a traditional feel by decorating with many old fashion items while keeping the environment tidy and clean. The pricing is more expensive than the markets in the urban areas though is in line with other markets in Tung Chung.
